# Implementation Plan - Step-by-Step RAG Integration using Qdrant

This plan details the step-by-step implementation of the Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system inside the existing SKAPS AI chatbot project. The architecture consists of a Python/FastAPI backend and a React/Next.js frontend.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Qdrant Vector Database Connection**: The backend will connect to Qdrant at `http://localhost:6333` (configured in `.env`). Please make sure a local Qdrant container or cloud cluster is running.
> You can launch Qdrant locally using Docker:
> ```bash
> docker run -p 6333:6333 -p 6334:6334 -v qdrant_storage:/qdrant/storage qdrant/qdrant
> ```

> [!TIP]
> **Automatic Processing Integration**: Instead of duplicating upload and deletion endpoints, we will hook the RAG text extraction, chunking, and embedding ingestion directly into the existing Knowledge Base endpoints (`/api/admin/documents/upload` and `/api/admin/documents/{doc_id}`). This ensures documents uploaded via the admin panel are processed and semantically indexed in Qdrant automatically!

